{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-967].
  {panel}

It would be useful if the table that is outputed by the macro {jiraissues:URL} would allow you to click on the title of the rows to alter the sorting - but just temporarily (i.e. not change the page code itself, just adapt the url on output).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-954].
  {panel}

Currently templates cant be applied to profiles. It would be useful to have a profile template for the company employee's and one for clients so that internally we can store their email address, direct dial, extn etc - and the client the same except no extension and a switch board number instead.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-922].
  {panel}

If the RSS macro retrieves an HTML page by mistake, parse the page for its <title> and display that title as part of the error message: that way the user gets a clue as to what they're retrieving instead.

e.g. if the title is "Confluence - Login"...
